dc:description: Cranium without a calotte. Large inca bone that is larger on the R half, large osteophyte and pitting lesions on floor of left middle cranial fossa superomedial petrosal ends in processes directed toward dorsum sella, osteophytes beginning to cover internal opening of f. spinosum; osteophyte lateral to fa. ovale (bilateral). Mandible has a few broken teeth present; alveolar resorption of incisors, R&L molars and L premolars.
